	<h2>About</h2>
	<p>I am currently a postdoctoral researcher at the <a href="http://www.ics.forth.gr/cvrl">Computer Vision and Robotics Laboratory (CVRL)</a> of the <a href="http://www.ics.forth.gr/">Institure of Computer Science (ICS)</a> at the <a href="http://www.forth.gr/">Foundation for Research and Technology-Hellas (FORTH)</a>, working with Professor <a href="http://www.ics.forth.gr/~argyros">A. A. Argyros</a>.</p>
	<p>My research mainly regards computational methods for observing and understanding the interaction of human and robotic systems with objects of their environment. Other research interests regard Computer Vision, Physics Simulation, Computer Graphics, Software Engineering and Performance Computing. I have a programming experience over several platforms, i.e. various Operating Systems, Programming Languages and Target Hardware. For more information please refer to my academic <a href="media/cv.pdf">CV</a>.</p>
	<p>I can be contacted through <a title="Reveal this e-mail address" href="http://www.google.com/recaptcha/mailhide/d?k=017KWG_KpTYVYRvB7SsTqX-Q==&c=x7_RDsIJelsjbgxumIBQeRqdoAdEVFNrkY1XeUNupEI=">e-mail</a>. More information is provided in my <a href="media/CV.pdf">CV</a>.</p>
